I'm a junior researcher in science of science and education sciences with economics and econometrics background. Currently I work at European University at St.Petersburgin and seeking a challenging Ph.D. position to study the origins of gender disparities and generate actionable policies. I am eager to work on a project that allows me to develop my skills in network and textual analysis, machine learning, and causal inference. I'm proficient in statistics, data collection, preprocessing, exploratory and statistical data analysis, data visualization (R, Python).
